Over 1.9 million candidates are taking the 2020 Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination which commenced on Saturday across the country. The examination will be holding in 700 centers in the 36 states of the federation and Abuja.
The examination which started last Saturday is expected to extend to April 4th, 2020.
At the beginning of the examination on Saturday in Abuja, systems failure, poor electricity, lateness were noticed during the Unified Tertiary matriculation examinations. It is expected that there will be improvement in these challenges in subsequent conduct of the examination in other centers.
